ini (also using the Snapdragon 865) is $199. Although we don\u0026#39;t yet know how much the Flip 2 will cost, it\u0026#39;s likely safe to assume that the Dimensity 1100 model could start at $249, with a $20 or $30 increase for the SD865 variant.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv data-hydrate=\"true\" id=\"slice-container-newsletterForm-articleInbodyContent-CyYsNJQ3RnViVLZ62qjugh\"\u003e\u003csection\u003e\u003cp\u003eGet the latest news from Android Central, your trusted companion in the world of Android\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cfigure data-bordeaux-image-check=\"\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-320-80.jpg.webp 320w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-480-80.jpg.webp 480w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-650-80.jpg.webp 650w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-970-80.jpg.webp 970w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-1024-80.jpg.webp 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-1200-80.jpg.webp 1200w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1000px) 970px, calc(100vw - 40px)\"/\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-320-80.jpg\" alt=\"Color options grid for the Retroid Pocket Flip 2\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-320-80.jpg 320w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-480-80.jpg 480w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-650-80.jpg 650w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-970-80.jpg 970w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-1024-80.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K-1200-80.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1000px) 970px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" loading=\"lazy\" data-original-mos=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K.jpg\" data-pin-media=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/mnHHR5Hms3DwmqgLnwnR3K.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cfigcaption itemprop=\"caption description\"\u003e\u003cspan itemprop=\"copyrightHolder\"\u003e(Image credit: Retroid)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn addition to revealing the entire spec sheet, Retroid also provided everyone with a look at the four different color options consisting of Ice Blue, GC, 16Bit US, and Black. Both the GC and 16Bit US are carry-overs from the Retroid Pocket 5, with the exception of the buttons on the Pocket Flip 2.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHowever, based on reactions on social media and Discord, Ice Blue seems to be the early fan favorite. This isn\u0026#39;t all that surprising, given that the same was true when the Retroid Pocket 4 and 4 Pro were released in the Ice Blue colorway. The only real disappointment is that the Watermelon (transparent red) doesn\u0026#39;t appear to be in the plans.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMuch like how smartphone companies operate nowadays, these retro handheld makers like to trickle out little bits of information slowly. Such is the case with the Retroid Pocket Flip 2, so we\u0026#39;ll be keeping our eyes out for when pricing and availability information are provided.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePhone deals: \u003c/strong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://shop-links.co/link?id=pcmcat1563302848653\u0026amp;publisher_slug=future\u0026amp;exclusive=1\u0026amp;u1=ac-us-1288088828302794453\u0026amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fsite%2Ftop-deals%2Fcell-phone-deals%2Fpcmcat1563302848653.c%3Fid%3Dpcmcat1563302848653\u0026amp;article_name=New%20Galaxy%20A56%20and%20A36%20renders%20surface%20indicating%20an%20imminent%20launch%20%7C%20Android%20Central\u0026amp;article_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.androidcentral.com%2Fphones%2Fnew-galaxy-a56-and-galaxy-a36-renders-surface\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored noopener\" data